Specifically, it focuses on finding disimplicial arcs, recognizing graph classes defined by their existence, and developing algorithms for disimplicial elimination schemes. These topics are closely related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.LG) due to its algorithmic focus.
